    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <head>No. 392.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName corresp="#p_DES1" type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Received Feb. 16—5.5 p.m.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 16,
                            1873</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have communicated your telegrams of 12th and 14th to this government, and am
                        requested by President <persName>Figueras</persName> to convey to you the
                        expressions of satisfaction and appreciation with which our friendly
                        assurances have been received. My speech and that of the President in reply
                        were afterward read to the assembly by <persName>Castelar</persName>, and
                        received with general applause.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DES1">SICKLES</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
